
Did you know git has a command that does all of this for us?

i.e. It can take a file or file contents, construct this git
object format, compress it, and then save the file with the
correct sha1.

-------------------------------------------------------

echo 'Holi mis mieles' | git hash-object --stdin -w

->

-------------------------------------------------------

38570a2fc50247a315ccc922863ae5d052781d67

Question:

Are we missing any information in the blob?

